title: Vyleen White's Daughter Speaks Out After Teen Murderer Sentenced | 10 News+
description: The teenager who murdered a Queensland grandmother has been given a 16 year sentence, but will only serve just under 10 years before being paroled. He was found guilty of stabbing 70-year-old Vyleen White to death in front of her 6-year-old granddaughter in a shopping centre carpark in Ipswich last year. He cannot be identified because he is under 18 years old. title: Liberals Ditch Net Zero Target, Trump Lashes Out Over Epstein Emails, Gen Z’s Pessimism | 10 News+
description: The Liberal Party has formally announced it will ditch its net zero by 2050 target, following in the footsteps of their Nationals colleagues. Liberal leader Sussan Ley says their priority is on reducing energy prices for Australians, and Nationals leader David Littleproud insists his party believes in the science of climate change. Meanwhile, Prime Minister Albanese called the Coalition a “clown show” that is internally divided.  The teenager who murdered a Queensland grandmother has been given a 16 year sentence, but will only serve just under 10 years before being paroled. He was found guilty of stabbing 70-year-old Vyleen White to death in front of her 6-year-old granddaughter in a shopping centre carpark in Ipswich last year. He cannot be identified because he is under 18 years old.  A 76-year-old woman who’s been working on her farm her whole life has found herself unable to be buried next to her husband, because the land has been rezoned by the government. Gaye Wheatley, and dozens of farmers in central New South Wales, have been threatened with fines if they touch the soil or the trees on the land they have toiled on for generations.  Patti LaBelle, the ‘Godmother of Soul’, has announced she will be touring Australia next year. The 81-year-old is behind hits like ‘Lady Marmalade’, ‘On My Own’, and ‘If You Ask Me To’. She spoke to Georgie Tunny for 10 News+ about her extraordinary career spanning six decades, and why you should never call her a diva.
